article.description: Maria Getty scored 12 points, Laura Kurz added 10 points and nine rebounds and Villanova won its seventh straight game, 50-46 over No. 25 DePaul on Saturday.
article.headline: Wildcats win eighth straight in Big East; Karcic reaches 1,000-point mark
article.linkText: Villanova 9-2 in Big East, beats No. 25 DePaul
article.story:
VILLANOVA, Pa. -- Maria Getty scored 12 points, Laura Kurz added 10 points and nine rebounds and Villanova won its seventh straight game, 50-46 over No. 25 DePaul on Saturday.

Lisa Karcic contributed eight points to eclipse 1,000 for her career. It was the Wildcats' second win in a row over a ranked opponent, having beaten Notre Dame 55-48 (then ranked No. 9 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP) on Jan. 24.

Villanova (17-8, 9-2 Big East), which won for the first time in five tries against DePaul, has its best Big East record since the 1994-95 season. The Wildcats also won their eighth straight conference game, their longest streak since winning the final eight games of the 2003-04 season.

Sam Quigley scored 13 points and Natasha Williams added 11 for DePaul (19-7, 7-5), which had won six of seven entering the game.

Quigley hit a layup with 11:52 remaining to give the Blue Demons a 38-36 lead. But they went 9:35 without another field goal, hitting just one of two free throws as Villanova took a 46-39 lead with 4:19 remaining.

DePaul battled back within 47-46 on a layup by Keisha Hampton with 9 seconds left, but Williams was whistled for an intentional foul on Kurz with 4.2 seconds remaining. She made one of two free throws, and Siobhan O'Connor sealed the victory with a pair of free throws with 3.3 seconds to go.

DePaul shot just 36 percent (18-of-50) and hit only 1-of-13 from 3-point territory.
